                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="1r" to="1v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Computistical tables</title>
                                <incipit>Post xvi kalendas februarias ubi luna fuerit decima</incipit>
                                <explicit defective="false">Aetas uero lune paschalis numquam minor est quam xv. nec maior quam xxi.</explicit>
                                <note>The text ends on <locus from="1v" to="1v" scheme="folios"/> with a table showing the <quote>Claves terminorum</quote>, <quote>Regulares terminorum</quote>, <quote>Paschalis terminus</quote> and <quote>Epacte</quote>.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="2r" to="7v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Calendar</title>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        As noted by <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107221">Friedl (1927)</title>
                                            <citedRange from="132" to="132" unit="page"/>
                                        </bibl>, saints are mentioned on all days in the calendar.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        Notable feasts:</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/>: St Aldegund (30 Jan.) </p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="3r" to="3r" scheme="folios"/>: Translation of St Weneclas (4 Mar.) </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="3r" to="3r" scheme="folios"/>: St Ludger (26 Mar.) </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="3v" to="3v" scheme="folios"/>: Sts Adalbert and St George (23 Apr.) </p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="4r" to="4r" scheme="folios"/>: St Gotthard (4 May) </p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="4r" to="4r" scheme="folios"/>: St Gangolf (13 May) </p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="5r" to="5r" scheme="folios"/>: St Zorard (17 July) </p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="5r" to="5r" scheme="folios"/>: St Ulrich; Translation of St Martin (4 Oct.)</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="5r" to="5r" scheme="folios"/>: St Willibald (7 July) </p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="5v" to="5v" scheme="folios"/>: St Oswald (5 Aug.) </p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="6r" to="6r" scheme="folios"/>: St Maurice (22 Sep.) </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="6r" to="6r" scheme="folios"/>: St Wenceslas (28 Sep.) </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="6v" to="6v" scheme="folios"/>: St Wolfgang of Regensburg (31 Oct.) </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="7r" to="7r" scheme="folios"/>: St Ludmila (10 Nov.) </p>
                                    <p>
                                        The calendar has also been used as a necrology; see further <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107235">Bistřický (2011)</title>
                                            <citedRange from="77" to="85" unit="page"/>
                                        </bibl>.</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p/>
                                </note>
                                <listBibl>
                                    <bibl>
                                        <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107234">Dudík (1880)</title>
                                        <citedRange from="3" to="16" unit="page"/>
                                    </bibl>
