                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="8r" to="9r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Computistical tables</title>
                                <incipit defective="false">Anni ab inicio mundi</incipit>
                                <explicit defective="false">Propter hoc ipso anno nulle epacte dicuntur et exhinc xi pronuntia</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="9v" to="9v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Bloodletting table</title>
                                <rubric>Argumentum ad discernendas utilitates siue ad minuendum sanguinem</rubric>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="10r" to="17v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Ferial psalter (interrupted)</title>
                                <rubric>Dominicis diebus inuitatorium</rubric>
                                <incipit>Adoremus dominum qui fecit nos (Ps. 94:6)</incipit>
                                <explicit defective="true">Dominum Deum nostrum venite adoremus</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p> The section begins with the invitatory antiphon for Sunday and ends with the Invitatory antiphon for Saturday. The Ferial psalter continues on <locus from="154r" to="154r" scheme="folios"/>; the pages have been separated as a result of the re-binding of the volume.</p>
                                    <p/>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="18r" to="30v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Common of saints</title>
                                <rubric>In nataliciis apostolorum ad uesperas Capitulum</rubric>
                                <incipit>BENEDICCIO DOMINI super caput iusti (Prov. 10:6)</incipit>
                                <explicit>earum intercessionibus commendemur et meritis. Per dominum</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        Collects and chapters for the following feasts:</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="18r" to="19r" scheme="folios"/>: Common of apostles;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="19r" to="20r" scheme="folios"/>: Common of two apostles;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="20r" to="21r" scheme="folios"/>: Common of evangelists;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="21r" to="22v" scheme="folios"/>: Common of a martyr;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="22v" to="23r" scheme="folios"/>: Common of a martyr and pope;</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="23r" to="24v" scheme="folios"/>: Common of martyrs;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="24v" to="26v" scheme="folios"/>: Common of a confessor bishop;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="26v" to="28r" scheme="folios"/>: Common of a confessor not a pope;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="28r" to="28v" scheme="folios"/>: Common of many confessors;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="28v" to="30r" scheme="folios"/>: Common of virgins;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="30r" to="31v" scheme="folios"/>: Common of many virgins.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="30v" to="33r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Dedication of the church and the altar</title>
                                <rubric>IN DEDICATIONI AECCLESIE AD VESPERAS CAPITVLVM</rubric>
                                <incipit>UIDI CIVITATEM Sanctam hierusalem nouam (Rev. 21:2)</incipit>
                                <explicit>ab omnibus hic inuocantibus nomen tuum protectionis tue auxilium senciatur. Per dominum</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        Collects and chapters.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="33v" to="34r" scheme="folios"/>: Blank. <locus from="34v" to="34v" scheme="folios"/>: Miniature.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="35r" to="104v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="uniform">Proper of time</title>
                                <incipit>DEVS PACIS SANCTIFICET UOS PER omnia (1 Thess. 5:23)</incipit>
                                <explicit>et habitabunt in terra sua dicit dominus omnipotens</explicit>
                                <note>Collects and chapters. The proper of time begins with the First Sunday of Advent and ends with the twenty-fifth Sunday after Pentecost.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="105r" to="153r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Proper of saints</title>
                                <rubric>IN FESTUM SANCTI ANDREE apostoli Capitulum ad uesperas</rubric>
                                <incipit>BEATVS UIR qui facit iudicium et iusticiam</incipit>
                                <explicit>pio iugiter experiamur auxilio. Per dominum</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <locus from="153v" to="153v" scheme="folios"/>: Blank. The proper of saints begins with St Andrew (30 Dec.) and ends with Sts Saturninus, Crysanthus, Maurus and Daria (29 Nov.) </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="154r" to="154v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Ferial psalter (continued)</title>
                                <incipit defective="false">Quia mirabilia fecit dominus (Ps. 97:1)</incipit>
                                <explicit defective="unknown">in conspectu tuo acceptabile sacrificium uespertinum per dominum</explicit>
                                <note>The text continues from <locus from="17v" to="17v" scheme="folios"/> with the antiphons, chapters and prayers for Saturday.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="154v" to="155r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Votive offices</title>
                                <rubric>DE SANCTA TRINITATE</rubric>
                                <incipit>Quis deus magnus sicut deus noster (Ps. 76:14)</incipit>
                                <explicit>et angelica prestitisti suffragia non desse per Christum</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        Versicles and collects to the following offices:</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="154v" to="154v" scheme="folios"/>: The holy Trinity;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="155r" to="155r" scheme="folios"/>: the holy cross;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="155r" to="155r" scheme="folios"/>: the Virgin;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="155r" to="155r" scheme="folios"/>: the angels.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="155r" to="157v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="uniform">Suffrages</title>
                                <incipit>PERPETVVUM NOBIS domine me miserationis presta subsiduum</incipit>
                                <explicit>absolutos in tua faciat pace gaudentes per dominum</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        Versicles and collects to the following suffrages:</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="155v" to="155v" scheme="folios"/>: St John the Baptist;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="155v" to="155v" scheme="folios"/>: the apostles;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="155v" to="155v" scheme="folios"/>: St Vitus;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="155v" to="155v" scheme="folios"/>: St Wenceslaus;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="156r" to="156r" scheme="folios"/>: St Adalbert;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="156r" to="156r" scheme="folios"/>: St Benedict and his companions;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="157v" to="157v" scheme="folios"/>: St Martin;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="157v" to="157v" scheme="folios"/>: St Nicholas;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="157v" to="157v" scheme="folios"/>: St Giles;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="158r" to="158r" scheme="folios"/>: St Mary Magdalene;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="158r" to="158r" scheme="folios"/>: St Ludmila the Martyr;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="158r" to="158r" scheme="folios"/>: All saints.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="158r" to="158v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="uniform">Chapters and collects for Compline</title>
                                <rubric>AD COMPLETORIVM Capitulum</rubric>
                                <incipit>TV IN NOBIS ES DOMINE et nomen tuum sanctum et gloriosum</incipit>
                                <explicit>sed dextera tua inuicta nos custodiat per dominum</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="159r" to="161v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Office for the dead</title>
                                <rubric>In die depositionis defuncti </rubric>
                                <incipit>DEUS CVI PRIMVM est misereri semper ac parcere</incipit>
                                <explicit defective="true">Maiestatem tuam domine supplices exoramus ut anime famularum tuarum N ab omnibus</explicit>
                            </msItem>
